claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Multi‐panel figure showing ELISA antibody titers against egg‐derived and cell‐derived HA (A), Egg/Cell HA ELISA titer ratios (B), HA stalk ELISA titers (C), and HA stalk titer fold‐rise (D) at Day 0, 1 month, and 6 months post‐vaccination for four vaccine groups: Fluzone IIV4, Fluarix IIV4, ccIIV4, and RIV4. Evidence: The figure presents immunogenicity data (antibody titers and fold‐rise) for RIV4 (recombinant vaccine) versus standard IIV4 vaccines but does not show HA antigen content or any 3× dosing information. The figure shows greater immunogenicity for RIV4 versus standard‐dose vaccines but does not provide any data on HA antigen content or a 3× dosage comparison; therefore, it does not support the claim Note: The image text is legible and clear, but dosing information is not included; conclusions about antigen content cannot be drawn from the presented immunogenicity data.
